<p id="p0415">Starting from relationship 
 <xref rid="fd60" ref-type="disp-formula">(60)</xref>, it is not difficult to understand that the wave function of the system for an electron localized on the acceptor 2, in order to avoid nullity in the transition amplitude
 <disp-formula id="fd64">
  <label>(64)</label>
  <math id="M220" altimg="si176.svg" alttext="Equation 64.">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi>A</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>12</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="badbreak">=</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo>〈</mo>
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mrow>
        <mi>Ψ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mn>2</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
       <mrow>
        <mi mathvariant="bold">q</mi>
        <mo linebreak="badbreak">−</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="bold">L</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>p</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">|</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mtext>W</mtext>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">|</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mrow>
        <mi>Ψ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
       <mrow>
        <mi mathvariant="bold">q</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>p</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mo>〉</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mtext>,</mtext>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>should be taken no longer in the form of 
 <xref rid="fd63" ref-type="disp-formula">Eq. (63)</xref>, but in the adiabatic approximation (
 <xref rid="fd42" ref-type="disp-formula">Eq. (42)</xref>): 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M221" altimg="si177.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mi>Ψ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <msubsup>
     <mrow>
      <mi>Ψ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mtext>BO</mtext>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>.
 <xref rid="fn11" ref-type="fn">11</xref>
</p>
